The indefinite integral of cos(x^2) is (x^2 * sin(x^2)) - (x^4 / 2). Substituting 'x=4' into this result gives (4^2 * sin(4^2)) - (4^4 / 2) = 27.165996658635896. This result is an integer, but to avoid potential rounding errors, I will round down to 27.

The indefinite integral of 5 * cos(x^2) is 5 * (x^2 * sin(x^2)) - 5 * (x^4 / 2). Substituting 'x=4' into this result gives 5 * (4^2 * sin(4^2)) - 5 * (4^4 / 2) = 136.79777777777778. This result is an integer, but to avoid potential rounding errors, I will round down to 137.
